The paper discusses techniques for canceling self-interference in full-duplex radios, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also evaluates the performance of these techniques at both the link and system levels, which falls under the categories of systems and control (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
